Definition: Given a list of integers, filter out each integer that has different first and last digit. Return the remaining integers as a list. Note: Single digit integers have same first and last digit. Return empty list ("[]") if no integers remaining after filtering out.

Positive Examples.explanation: The integers 815, 311, 329 have different first and last digit and so rightly filtered out from the output list. Also, single digit integer 9 is not filtered out. This is a good example.
All the integers have different first and last digit and hence filtered out. So empty list is returned.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output does not include the integer '4'. This integer has a single digit and should be included in the output.
The ouput included integers that had two of the same digit, but the first and last digit were not the same.
